==English==
{{wikipedia}}
====Etymology====
Via Spanish, a corruption of [[Swahili]] ''ki denga pepo'', meaning "cramp-like seizure caused by an evil spirit". 
===Noun===

{{en-noun|-}}
# {{pathology}} An acute febrile and sometimes hemorrhagic disease endemic to the [[tropics]], caused by any of four species of the virus [[genus]] ''[[wikipedia:Flavivirus|Flavivirus]]'', and primarily transmitted to humans from mosquitoes, though human-to-human transmission is also well documented. 

====Synonym====
*[[breakbone fever]]